Subject: 🎆 Diwali Special! New Prompt Engineering Course + 90%
Body:
New Promotional Announcement

Hi Keerthika an announcement has been made from Chetan instructor of UI/UX Design With Figma : 5+ Real World Projects.

🎉🎆 Diwali Special & Exciting News! The ChatGPT Prompt Engineering Mastery Course is Here 🎉


I’m thrilled to announce the launch of my latest course on Udemy: The ChatGPT Prompt Engineering Mastery Course! 🎉 And here’s some great news—it’s already become Udemy’s highest-rated prompt engineering course with over 3000 students joining in just five days. This response has been beyond amazing and I couldn't wait to share this journey with you!


This course is designed with YOU in mind. Whether you’re in tech business content creation or simply curious about AI this course has a little something for everyone. Prompt engineering is much more than just understanding how AI works—it’s about unlocking your creativity boosting productivity and finding smarter ways to tackle everyday challenges. Imagine automating your repetitive tasks creating engaging content with ease or even exploring new tools like ChatGPT Google Bard and more all in one place.


Here’s what you can expect:

✨ Real-World Applications – This course isn’t just theory; it’s packed with projects! You’ll find practical exercises for creating prompts that save time enhance productivity and bring your ideas to life.

✨ Powerful Prompt Patterns – Dive into advanced techniques like Few-Shot Learning and Persona Patterns. From business automation to creative projects you’ll learn how to structure prompts for any purpose.

✨ Future-Ready Skills – As AI becomes central to every industry mastering prompt engineering could give you a powerful edge whatever your career path might be.


And the best part? It’s all in bite-sized lessons under 10 minutes so you can learn at your own pace and see immediate real-world benefits. My goal is to make this journey as enjoyable and impactful as possible—think of it as a toolkit that will grow with you in today’s AI-driven world.


Link: The ChatGPT Prompt Engineering Mastery Course! (Diwali Offer 90% Off)

Thank you for your continuous support and enthusiasm—it truly means the world to me! If you're ready to dive in I’d love for you to join us and start mastering the art of prompt engineering.

Happy Diwali! 🌟 To celebrate the festival of lights I'm excited to offer you 90% off on all my bestselling courses! Subject: The overwhelmed person’s guide to AI with Google Cloud: October 31
Body: The overwhelmed person’s guide to AI with Google Cloud by Chloe Condon   <https://notifications.google.com/g/p/ANiao5o2n-7H0sC4L26INKia5xDT54_UgdTL1MVqeoGBP-493qvXDOf8SxQkcHtSb01EZ15nVy746dbjOAyU9wC-KL40v3n7XxIAy2RO3frSAr54O1r_G5brjvJTao4FqqEQnDJ2crLMKYGqwY4KHNwXJy74yJW1-oApcx-iietYQX1QH4E3qWFJKJhqoKNVV4mAr9r-FUUmb2Rqfy8y8DwqkdxvpMu13bQqBw>  Welcome back to another month of The Overwhelmed Person's Guide to AI with   Google Cloud! A monthly digest of all the content announcements events   and learning resources I’ve been gathering over the last couple weeks to   share with you all.  This month I’ve been focused on sharpening my AI knowledge- which means a   lot of my time has been spent learning brand new concepts pair programming   with teammates and participating in hackathons using our AI tools. I was   feeling a bit overwhelmed but then I remembered: I write “The Overwhelmed   Person’s Guide to AI with Google Cloud” So feeling overwhelmed is   technically a case study… right? Right (at least that’s what I’m going to   tell myself to feel a little less overwhelmed in the meantime).  Hopefully this month’s newsletter makes you feel a little less overwhelmed   and a lot more excited to learn what you can build using AI. I can’t wait   to see what you build!  New and shiny  Three new things I had to share!  A podcast version of your NotebookLM sources.  As a frequent podcast listener this got me really excited! NotebookLM now   lets you listen to a conversation about your sources-   <https://notifications.google.com/g/p/ANiao5oYuHvGAWzXfFTiERydh9A_qik7Xqb8IvArMqr-y-RFKCAUVRTTPCRbv86YXaTFc47Tl2XzKIdCpftkYLlwS3owo9_lhHzQhCLbIfNSPOd4LaWsjqv-Z0rzShuF2eG4aD0yWbRQ-V0mQKd3nf4U4Ou00flDttmpve8E8tf0eW-MSan9WoWVXalqvQVD2VYg3RAasZYnRq2VWZkTToWfC46PrNRomNdUZZOW7TvmE6en60vvaXdQEEXymj6YRBs4y1ofXrCxbrtVlmiOxkRyYPmeyRiXzQygZAAa1FgmC38>   no really! With one click two AI hosts start up a lively “deep dive”   discussion based on your sources. They summarize your material make   connections between topics and banter back and forth. You can even   download the conversation and take it on the go. It’s literally like   listening to a podcast about your notebook! 🎧  Anthropic’s upgraded Claude 3.5 Sonnet on Vertex AI.  This month we announced the general availability of the upgraded Claude 3.5   Sonnet for US customers <https://notifications.google.com/g/p/ANiao5pEegGgijhvHm-1hBICGb95zg0KGJlXf8Hm6s9bvailHLQUiSCIwH35731tCp48Mkv3BJI2qtqxJ8ajt8CEIZvlJdeCp38tuM6iTsIx82NGZJqZX8JoE3SMbTZrAO_XYoGe2gLNPwnPCiIBf77bNpLVsLxw2RpC7CFkiERPUJcU-Eak8G9YH_IehO2VQ3WXaRS_V9yUh8E_1LrvedpWJbCDnV6HO0yypgfCbJQjCOLpC39Vfl2ivoURzJRgCkv0QQ1uDR4baUWe823RMD3JGt4nPUfQWPBOpVUACPBt-WIyXl11inhu0S_hQM-39npxLOM-mqwHiV-HVTTfSbNPAAlqCBt9fp2mJe1wBhcjr-l7njrzrjgDS0CTBxUemYcM3X8>   featuring   a new “computer use” capability in public beta on Vertex AI   Model Garden.   <https://notifications.google.com/g/p/ANiao5peNk5-t4ahweLceO2X7z_KLrMJVOo3beKCtKPkspTKe_R2Xuon0r5lgN8AYkp2WC9PofoBTG7tVnNd0Lqbez7VINUtF0IcKlYy2WeDeIfS6Q-g8tXkLsfAhNB4DYlsO4DlySpdinYPbIP7L8GyV4o4WajNkKhIhw2knAEbtfyeXVAI-Qu7yyKzjyqTS_frgpw7taFrvSomg3m7ItvfAtNrBwPobuOohktzUWNSWZzbOEybTld1Q6to0MG28b5hRsJ4d-grCQ>   With this upgrade you’ll be able to experiment with confidence on Vertex   AI without worrying about complex deployment processes build sophisticated   AI agents and build with enterprise-grade security and compliance with   Google Cloud's built-in security privacy and compliance measures. The   best part? You can get started and manage without overhead with fully   managed infrastructure designed for AI workloads. Check out the blog post <https://notifications.google.com/g/p/ANiao5q5MSj4udau7yJiAoSojKPWocaenpps_dn5_Q5oH4JvCsgBhXj_9BtUnIB7-AjubZ-U3-g88VL0k-NyRPAsbt7rKIFVCtcARUG6f4-wPB-P2fAjXi-2qsmeOFvPzQ6hIkDRvJnZL4FfI5ObDwm06RkWpOg6DPxVrckEPcqxGdZAL3ztCKcdxA78DpIaZo1M_2LcQ3Eozqh129XvrXDrRda7tNgqVWzM7NZs7SwLtHfkYs0rCwk1eAUsaPBzAM96bp935n9ohdhi9mrkHb7sHz6su22M02iZluYDBfSV0wlllhuzmL62Lx_MBxBj8vX6AbNbxZevN2TgaN09k46DfwEffc21aZlX>to   learn   more!  Choosing the right gen AI partner.  Earlier this month Google hosted the Google Cloud Startup Summit   <https://notifications.google.com/g/p/ANiao5p_wK8OKdeku3ICZcIAuQxA6XjkFRZingxF-rAQ7qZypgl_7vLcUMX6NeRISwpZfwPx2SxdL0OXd2PVzNDdtuwQJBod4CtuNx6Pccgd4u8QT4aR8KJfQ2e0u_v5afopqc1MqgJateNQzbJ0F_j5u8i0Ea-5t2lAqguOw5ZIrmnbeqyit0yXhZbGSzblBRe3FTMWzyt6XFiv3AcGboU0kBGtkRnRA7uaOKU29nnV6XPJMl2TtyI8KciKSprtQt1CDM60f_eIjzyXZr8zT2XO_d-AhyJnZBxvFnaJ>   where we gathered a stellar lineup of experts leading VCs and   entrepreneurs to share their recommendations for accelerating your   startup’s journey. If you missed it- don’t worry! You can watch the entire   summit online. Be sure to watch the session Choosing the right gen AI   partner   <https://notifications.google.com/g/p/ANiao5ooNUR3ob5wqDe1f2aOU_DuyEyl4xlGNJ7qAzxhnj1ZCuVCcbBA9wDCW99c_5UVdMLuZLJPhyge2Xy6d7UU5koffaiyY9aX4StyxA90zln7gnppsu-yjUzeQh8nUXkeHDBnXx_BLb038qW6DtTu-WZfpTI1VdFsy0QIlgOhHpmxOJwEnX1UNGTcZYFDY4QbR6nM3u2aPL_8b8LNrYtrloZXIzkxS3XdfO8YvvHU0P9PldrQs24_flVsxOQlg2O5VS5dzpFenCa5uMcBaFcmO8Mrt-hn-6VLeNvDad0U17icU-UGa1EzcD_1p2PlEPvwk5v4s9kwwFPTkBs3FwOs3dFvfc-9hNIK>   where you’ll learn how founders of Vellum and Reve AI considered cost   security scalability and other criteria as they evaluated gen AI   providers.  Flex your generative AI skills with four NEW learning paths on Google Cloud   Skills Boost.  You know the basics—now you want to test your skills. These courses and   labs   <https://notifications.google.com/g/p/ANiao5pKoNqOcEV5_JybkhAoJ8etYyPUDm8lIgv9TOxL0aInbLcJ439TXI4uZEFYbaTw2NgzsHYmkHL6kMTLlpTbOtn7RVt9eufJqeHMKW4xqaErHXjLPsp5208kf4UNdw4twmQiN-HLBGZ-K3cWOzJXHcZHTTfFlIaOwfin_434wtFXm_hJRmx7AaeK9YDbDHu6uawCNQMH8hgqEQkkud6HGdjnYL7Mrner-7yDe_qYROeZvUuQEVcKU7XmZN599dPz3OuWaN7ancmmVwoY7y5frI0QZiIyaFo3SHkOl53rUPAfn0ayWC3T1fSFsXk-TlSXCfru6BWQBwKPw21iCMVxkUqU6neYQTco0VHzduqozAqP4MegnZxGKuRQPvk1yMEOs-WlOzK1ibMb6RACNxBHT4B0q17ldJ3IYVNdzvihMN4jnQzSyWT9hFfdppigQc8ZQ3CkbKMA02Ie-HKqvdLz5aJyFsv83fFV_IqJzeciLHXzhXrjKeqQZYNRz7Huuxw>   show you how to apply gen AI to real-world use cases like building gen AI   applications modernizing web apps or managing gen AI models.  Hey Innovators Live Events!  Build Intelligent Apps with Spanner: Unifying Graph Vector and Full-Text   Search <https://notifications.google.com/g/p/ANiao5ry2VQINSDa1_M2Zjsma-jIgFpXfD86ifzIg64djzGW55aKBURzkYPEzwhExOacq4EW7DnKYw2YU2ua18W-JLyxvvxp7GkPGM_YAitqtbjM2-n7QyR0pl66oiT4GR8tLvlHoH0Cf3IcAebigBIdsyqylvFJXTC6DLIIOIZ_z0WZ-5YefNKmKMWVkWzGpNYOzAabtCUkxpcFBp9_0Z-zGMnabEwfktpB4rbaYyZOxixKsvnLxSyttVt5BZ3buKYZiLhktnX5MA5wfoRt6SxAb_NGPiMsk6YzQbv80DDyMiY6SXVIylN3EP2CEIAkm5WJ4odIjR9CavNdctKzaDRcGot1HEdSbgmkV9Izn8tUsAZRL9Aw5wB5R1oMZYkLDI8>  Unlock the power of Spanner to build intelligent AI apps! Combine graph   vector and full-text search in a single scalable database for faster data   insights and seamless scalability.  November 6 2024  11:00 AM - 12:00 PM PST 7:00 PM - 8:00 PM UTC  Register Today   <https://notifications.google.com/g/p/ANiao5pm44H5jBJMSNQyw9djmFi_T_ju7inY6eIhxO5X7NScXRcbIYcnecF-G03j_XgTRaQzAJvX6I8Xvmj1UMpuASMR9TUw1lpbs9HafH3RW8fZ-nOtDg97TU0DhnzQuNcYfSmVsGggtpqdTPDWTMkbPTMlmiLckDvJRxxtZFCeA6YK746vtTr3AR3w-wexMsOzjYBsB87UuRhfgLwpgkAcd0YywP336QsMkH_HSlaQi0cXuIxJLSvj4YpSva1WdpQaYfQnz8OiQ8vaHEUUoRczD-hOTo3Yik681AG54pRN84ntHYM52f4d15i2RykD18jIHdx94NR3oEEzg2M-MTTEffOVq7GFCayBhbXt7hfk4H6ReXaxgt3z9uQJoWZqfV8lX0GMwqX3upIsJp_-tBaiDnqPNO23v7LwCvtkj_BJVqJkOZA11-M7UIUIg2iPZjQLPPhm4VeBvxfV5oiaxb3wxbidGp079Cu1lrJVqfVg1BXYLRE-g9XcDWKm3bLCmnH8RoHtyiYgPARrKM1nK-muwYBtQeqNFg3jdM1tgV4NztBw8MmeExJLwyDY>  Building a Data Foundation for Your AI First Initiatives   <https://notifications.google.com/g/p/ANiao5pXwmO5ACcBvtmAp80cYmCll-7eoWqcFIS7qj8ZX5Pg1n4Dm-DbGzjx-NuDngxI-ooW21viXb3jYfzEOWn3LGCPZSxyzHAwlFtleG1GbVefwr69yTTd1c8a-p3SJwfyCdVp_siWr0j7DqDmVmencL4n7dMGgJeAPhtUtBMBoro4oVe8Nv-mdYj5k36syGLdbXhlYd-wACSbOiX2fQRTB8FmxDIObNEfmB5RBxy3wXge9mseRJZwvmTAVNzBLxgRcKtFWhR9bdsZGuAYaEi7u5qNhASPEVaJOBxcS7--DsxlvUbyr1JRxeKU0UWsdlsG-qGqKraV2j3vNEjZmcbnlBg>  A survey shows most companies prioritize AI but few succeed. Why? A weak   data foundation is often the culprit. Poor data leads to inaccurate AI   biased outcomes and wasted resources. Subject: How to use storytelling to engage stakeholders
Body: Career Chat  By Coursera   By Coursera                Read this article on LinkedIn to join the conversation Read on LinkedIn https://www.linkedin.com/comm/pulse/how-use-storytelling-engage-stakeholders-coursera-jzdme?lipi=urn%3Ali%3Apage%3Aemail_email_series_follow_newsletter_01%3Ba12vMx4yRsaxELtEdNnqFA%3D%3D&midToken=AQF2bg79cRmkSg&midSig=2muwdUMSrI3Xw1&trk=eml-email_series_follow_newsletter_01-null-0-read_more_banner_cta_&trkEmail=eml-email_series_follow_newsletter_01-null-0-read_more_banner_cta_-null-himwb0~m2xkh6nw~sa-null-null&eid=himwb0-m2xkh6nw-sa&otpToken=MTMwNTFiZTkxMDJjY2ZjN2JjMmUwZmViNDExZGU3Yjc4NmNhZDk0OTkwYWI4OTZjN2JjZjA0Njc0NzVjNTVmNWY0ZDBkN2U5NDZiN2VkZDk0N2E0Y2VhMDJjYWJlYjM5NGE0Mzc2ZTAzNWY3ZWNkOGM1NjBiYmYwLDEsMQ%3D%3D    👻Boo! Did that scare you?  If not it’s probably because it lacked one of the most critical ingredients of the jumpscare: surprise! That’s right whether we realize it or not that spine-tingling feeling many of us experience while watching a scary movie or reading a ghost story can actually be boiled down to a handful of basic elements organized and executed in just the right way. It’s a truly potent potion of craft and creativity that can make an audience shriek in terror.  Today in honor of Halloween and the spooky tales we love to tell we’re exploring the power of storytelling at work and in life. While we’ve previously discussed the importance of writing as a workplace skill storytelling transcends words on the page and can be found in everything from spoken presentations to data visualizations and even video game design. That transferability makes it valuable too. According to a study on workplace skills by McKinsey & Company high-income earners score notably higher on communication skills–including storytelling–than others.  So how can you start telling better stories in the workplace? It all starts with good bones.  🦴Structuring an engaging story Structure is one of the most important and overlooked elements of great storytelling. Structure refers to how a story is organized and presented to an audience whether that be a single reader nestled in an armchair or a packed audience at a conference. Put another way it’s the story’s skeleton that outlines its beginning middle and end.  There are many ways to structure your story but one of the most popular (and useful in the workplace) is the three-act structure which organizes a narrative into three distinct sections. You can use this structure to help tell your professional journey in a job interview lay out your resume or craft a team talk among other things. Here’s what the three-act structure looks like:  Set-up: The main character their relationships and the setting are established. Soon they encounter an obstacle that challenges them in some way known as “the inciting incident.”  Confrontation: The protagonist attempts to resolve the conflict but is unsuccessful usually due to a lack of skill and guidance. Eventually the character learns new skills and gains allies like a mentor that grant them a new understanding of themselves and the problem.    Resolution: The character uses their new skills and allies to overcome the initial conflict leading to an overall change in their world.  At its core the three-act structure is all about encountering a problem wrestling with it and then overcoming it with the right combination of skills and help. There are a lot of ways that you can apply the three-act structure in the workplace whether you’re giving a presentation writing a brief or designing a data visualization.  For example let’s say you’re preparing a slide deck at work about an initiative your team is undertaking. Considering the three-act structure you might first discuss how things looked before the initiative then describe the problems the initiative is trying to solve. Finally you’d conclude your presentation by focusing on the solution you settled on and its overall outcomes.  🧛Bite into storytelling courses Storytelling is a skill just like anything else. Build your strength as a storyteller in the workplace by biting into one of these courses: To motivate and influence audiences try McQuarie University’s Storytelling and influencing: Communicate with impact course.  For data-driven storytelling explore Google Cloud’s The Power of Storytelling: How to Visualize Data in the Cloud course.  For digital communication look into the University of Toronto’s Communication Strategies for a Virtual Age course. Plus for more tips check out Coursera’s podcast Still at Work which features an interview with course instructor Ivan Wanis Ruiz this week! Finally for a deep dive into leadership identity and creativity consider enrolling in the University of Colorado Boulder’s Storying the Self for Leadership and Creativity Specialization That’s all we’ve got for this issue. Before you head out to Trick or Treat let us know some of your storytelling tips in the comments below! See you next week.  Have a career question you’d like us to answer next? Share it below. And as always we welcome YOUR advice and experience in the comments.
